<BaseLayout
  title="Sign in — Blog"
  description="Sign in to the oriz blog to sync bookmarks across devices."
  hideSidebar={true}
  noindex={true}
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Blog</a> / Sign in</p>
    <h1>Sign in</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="prose">
    <p class="lede">
      Sign-in is optional. It is only used to sync your bookmarks across
      devices. The full blog content is readable without an account.
    </p>

    <h2>Email magic link</h2>
    <p>
      Sign-in uses Firebase email-link authentication. Enter your email and
      a one-time sign-in link will be sent. The link finishes the sign-in
      at <a href="/account/finish-sign-in/">/account/finish-sign-in</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      The sign-in widget is wired into the <a href="https://account.oriz.in/sign-in">account
      page</a>. This page is a placeholder so the policy footer links
      resolve cleanly.
    </p>

    <h2>What we store</h2>
    <p>
      Your email and a list of bookmarked slugs. Nothing else. See the
      <a href="/legal/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for details.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
